</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,912]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,310,461,487]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Remarks</emphasis>
: The description of 
<taxonomicName box="[551,814,461,486]" family="Macrodasyidae" genus="Macrodasys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="acrosorus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[551,814,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Macrodasys acrosorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[823,892,461,487]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[823,892,461,487]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is taken from a single specimen, the only one found (WDH video # 
<number box="[404,450,500,526]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="262.0">262</number>
, a 
<typeStatus box="[483,589,500,526]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<collectionCode box="[601,670,500,526]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">ICZN</collectionCode>
Articles 73.1. 
<number box="[837,852,500,526]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="2.0">2</number>
). Unusual is the ventral ciliation of paired lateral tracks, the homogeneous caudal organ, having fine spiral striations, and the longitudinally bilobed frontal organ with a beak-like apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="51" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,912]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,615,641]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Etymology:</emphasis>
The species is named for the sharply pointed beak-like tip (Greek: 
<emphasis box="[1185,1249,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">akros</emphasis>
) of the hollow (Greek: 
<emphasis box="[248,310,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">soros</emphasis>
) frontal organ.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,912]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,461,693,719]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Taxonomic affinities:</emphasis>
To the 
<number box="[562,591,693,719]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="28.0">28</number>
species currently in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[980,1120,693,718]" family="Macrodasyidae" genus="Macrodasys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[980,1120,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Macrodasys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are being added two new species 
<taxonomicName box="[245,404,732,757]" family="Macrodasyidae" genus="Macrodasys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="acrosorus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[245,404,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">M. acrosorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[412,482,731,757]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[412,482,731,757]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and one to be described below, bringing the number to 
<number box="[1157,1190,732,758]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="30.0">30</number>
. No other species of medium length in this genus has the following combination of characters: ventral ciliation with paired lateral tracks, a homogeneous caudal organ, having only fine spiral striations, and a longitudinally bilobed frontal organ with a beak-like apex, PhJIn at U 
<number box="[558,589,848,874]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="35.0">35</number>
, TbA 
<number box="[665,680,848,874]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="5.0">5</number>
per side, TbL/TbP 
<number box="[919,948,848,874]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="17.0">17</number>
/ 
<number box="[958,972,848,874]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="5.0">5</number>
per side, occurring regularly from the pharyngeal pores rearward.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
